The paper focuses on the application of Sum-Product Networks (SPNs) to image datasets, specifically color images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper introduces novel regularization methods for SPNs, which could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of SPNs for generative and discriminative tasks, which could also place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category.
